{WEST has 11 points and five \Hs, so she responds 
2\D as a Jacoby Transfer.

When EAST bids the required 2\H, WEST jumps to 3NT 
to show at least 11 points, but only a 5-card \H suit.

Since EAST has only a doubleton \H she passes 3NT.}

